                  <additions>
                     <p>On fiv v, Jones has written "Mīr Muhammad Husain May 1790 – The war-songs and some of the short pieces were written by the Prince of the Faithful, and, together with his Homilies, constitute all his works. The rest of the collection is believed to have been composed by another Ali ibn Abi Tālib of Kairouan or Cyrene." On f1v he has written "The Poems of ^Ali’".</p>
